folder: Beekman Street & Front Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Beekman Street, north side, west from Front, to and including Water Streets.

February 2, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Front Street & Beekman Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Front Street, east side, south from and including Beekman, to, but not including Fulton Streets. The view shows a garage occupying the western extremity of the Fulton Street Fish Market.

April 13, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH

folder: Front Street & Beekman Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Front Street, east side, south from and including Beekman, to, but not including Fulton Streets. The view shows a garage occupying the western extremity of the Fulton Fish Market. (Front Street, is arbitrarily set to run north and south between Coenties Slip, and the Brooklyn Bridge).

April 13, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Front Street & Beekman Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Front Street, north from Beekman Street. The Brooklyn Bridge is shown in the background. Front Street, is arbitrarily set to run north and south between Coenties Slip and the Brooklyn Bridge.

May 7, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH

folder: Front Street & Beekman Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
214-218 Front Street, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of Beekman Street. August 17, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.
